annotationA: TNF-receptor-associated factor-like, isoform A; It is involved in the biological process described with: defense response; signal transduction
annotationB: I-kappaB kinase epsilon (IKKepsilon) is a serine-threonine kinase that targets the inhibitor of apoptosis Diap1 for degradation. It also negatively regulates protein kinase C and the dynein adaptor nuf. IKKepsilon roles include specification of bristle cells, bristle cell morphogenesis, oocyte polarity, and dendrite development
